<headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 28 at 10:53PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Light Snow Over Central Montana Tonight...
Periods of light snow will effect parts of Central Montana
including areas around Stanford and Lewistown through 2 AM.
Visibility will be reduced to less than two miles at times.
New snow accumulations will range from around 1 inch at lower
elevations to 3 inches in the mountains.
Those traveling across Central Montana should be prepared for
slippery roadways and areas of reduced visibility.</description>
